[src:distributed-tracing-deep/instrumentation-computer-programming] Instrumentation enables profiling: measuring dynamic behavior during a test run.
[src:distributed-tracing-deep/instrumentation-computer-programming] This is useful for properties of a program that cannot be analyzed statically with sufficient precision, such as performance and alias analysis.
[src:distributed-tracing-deep/instrumentation-computer-programming] Instrumentation is limited by execution coverage.
[src:distributed-tracing-deep/instrumentation-computer-programming] If the program never reaches a particular point of execution, then instrumentation at that point collects no data.
[src:distributed-tracing-deep/instrumentation-computer-programming] For instance, if a word processor application is instrumented, but the user never activates the print feature, then the instrumentation can say nothing about the routines which are used exclusively by the printing feature.
[src:distributed-tracing-deep/instrumentation-computer-programming] Instrumentation increases the execution time of a program.
